originalText.text:
Cilantro surpassed all expectations with its enchanting atmosphere and outstanding culinary offerings. The ambiance seamlessly blends modern chic with cozy warmth, creating the perfect setting for an unforgettable dining experience. From the moment you step in, the inviting glow sets the tone for a delightful evening.

Now, let's talk about the food ‚Äì simply extraordinary. Each dish at Cilantro is a masterpiece, a symphony of flavors that dance on your taste buds. The menu is a culinary journey, featuring a delightful array of dishes that cater to diverse palates. The chef's commitment to using fresh, high-quality ingredients is evident in every bite.

The staff's attentiveness and knowledge add another layer to the overall excellence. Carlos the Gm is a tru gentle man. From recommendations to service, their dedication to ensuring guests have a memorable time is commendable. Cilantro isn't just a restaurant; it's an experience that leaves you craving more. If you're seeking a place where ambiance and cuisine harmonize to perfection, Cilantro is the epitome of culinary bliss.

originalText.text: The food looked good and a decent amount, however the skirt steak was undercooked( I asked for medium but it was mostly rare). The Guacamole was good but not really  spicy( I did ask for medium spice level though). The drink wasn't great I struggle to finish it and I can have quite a few. The waiter was good and attentive.  The atmosphere was good except for the customers with dogs that kept barking at each other and every other dog that passed by. I don't think I'll be returning.

originalText.text:
I have been coming here for a long time, and the food is absolutely delicious. My only problem now is I have been noticing the orders are getting smaller and smaller. The skirt steak used to be bigger; now it's a very small piece for that price. The drinks as well are getting weaker. What is going on? I still love the place, but portions are definitely smaller nowadays compared to before.

Additionally, I was saddened to discover that the menu no longer features the mussels, a dish I had previously enjoyed.
